.TH mpicxx 1 "@VERSION@" "@PACKAGE@" "MPI Commands" \" -*- nroff -*-
.SH NAME
mpicxx \- compile and link MPI programs written in C++
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mpicxx
[\fB\-hv\fR] [\fB\-CC=\fICXX\fR] [compile options]
.br
.B mpicc
[\fB\-hv\fR] [\fB\-CC=\fICXX\fR] [compile options]
.SH DESCRIPTION
These commands can be used to compile and link MPI programs written in
C++.  They provide the options and any special libraries that are
needed to compile and link MPI programs.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B -h
give short help.
.TP
.B -v
print version.
.TP
.B -CC=\fICXX\fR
set C++ compiler (default: configured compiler).

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR mpicc (1),
.BR mpiexec (1) .
